Now, OCA’s win-win decision last week seems to have set the stage for better diplomatic and economic relations between Doha, Riyadh and the Gulf in general.Sport, once again, has demonstrated its ability to unite the world, just as the famous “ping-pong diplomacy of the 1970s did in fostering good relations between China and USA through table tennis, or the 1914 “Christmas truce” football matches between Germany and Britain when the guns went silent.